			<img src="images/global/spacer.gif" width="100%" height="10" alt="*"><BR>
			<DIV CLASS="Content">
			<table border="0" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
				<TR>
					<td valign="top">
<SCRIPT LANGUAGE="JavaScript" SRC="js/DataValidation.js"></SCRIPT><B CLASS="HeadlineText">Medallion of Obulus</B><BR><BR><P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><I><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">This sub-quest is given by Slixin Klex at NEG 680, NEG 1130 in Burning Woods. He will be in one of the craters.</SPAN></I><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Garamond"> </SPAN><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">You say, 'Hail, Slixin Klex'<BR>Slixin Klex says 'So long ago... The burning of our land?<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">You say, 'What burning of our land?'<BR>Slixin Klex says 'Fiery death from the sky. Rock and fire burning our lands. Death and destruction splintering our tribe. Once, strong we were, but the fiery rocks from the sky crushed our proud cities and weakened our tribe.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">You say, 'What tribe?'<BR>Slixin Klex says 'Obulus was our people. The hills and trees were our lands. We tamed the dark and wilds and bent the forests to our needs. But all is gone, all our people, all our works, even the medallion that was the symbol of our power.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">You say, 'What medallion?'<BR>Slixin Klex says 'Medallion of the Obulus. Symbol of our proud people. Broken into pieces long lost to the dark forests now. I know where they are now but I am no longer flesh. If I were, I would find them and bring them back together.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<DIV align=center class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-ALIGN: center"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">
<HR align=center SIZE=2 width="100%">
</SPAN></FONT></DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Top Shard of the Obulus Medallion:<BR>You will first need a Burnished Wooden Stave, which drops off of random Sarnaks in Chardok. This is a tradeable item. Afterwards you will need to go to Ssolet Dnaas in Warslik Woods. I was kill on sight with him, and he sees through invisibility. Having an enchanter charm him is supposed to work, but I used Superior Camouflage then Sneaked to make him indifferent. After Ssolet Dnaas is indifferent to you, give him the Burnished Wooden Stave. <I>Ssolet Dnaas says 'Sssss. Thisss is what I need. You have my thanksss. Please, take thiss. I know not what it iss for but maybe you will find a ussse for it.</I> You then receive the Top Shard of the Obulus Medallion.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Middle Shard of the Obulus Medallion:<BR>This piece is dropped by the Rotting Skeleton in The Dreadlands. Head to 2246, NEG 5133 towards the North-East end of the zone. The Rotting Skeleton spawns at this location, with a Greater Plaguebone as the placeholder. This is a melee only mob. For a L60, the Rotting Skeleton will /CON light blue and be easy to solo. I had no resists to either snare or calcification.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Bottom Shard of the Obulus Medallion:<BR>This piece is dropped by the Pained Soul in Trakanon's Teeth. Head to NEG 1835, NEG 4368 near Sebilis. The Pained Soul spawns at this location, with a Spectral Keeper as the placerholder. There are other Spectral Keepers in the zone, but this mob does not wander. Both the Pained Soul and the Spectral Keeper are caster mobs. Some of the placerholders /CONed light blue in addition to the Pained Soul. I had no resists to either snare or calcification. The Pained Soul can hit anywhere from 40 to 100, so damage shields and chloroplast are recommended.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<DIV align=center class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-ALIGN: center"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">
<HR align=center SIZE=2 width="100%">
</SPAN></FONT></DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Once you have all three shards, return to Slixin Klex in Burning Woods.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><FONT size=1><SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">*Give Slixin Klex the Top, Middle and Bottom Shards for the Obulus Medallion.*<BR>Slixin Klex says 'Ssssss. I thought I would never see these. I never thought the symbol of our people would be made whole again. I feel no rest for my sssoul though. My torment still flows as freely as when my peoples first suffered fiery death. I need this not. It is useless to me. Here, you take it. Maybe you can find some good to do with it.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P><BR><BR><BR clear=all>
